-- Eskom's CEO Dames Says Strike Would Be Irresponsible, Threaten Power
-- Carli Lourens
-- 2010-06-30T17:08:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-30/eskom-s-ceo-dames-says-strike-would-be-irresponsible-threaten-power.html

          
          
             Eskom Holdings Ltd.’s Chief
Executive Officer Brian Dames said a strike by its workers would
be “premature and irresponsible” as the company is still in
talks over pay.  
 A strike would threaten the security of power supply and
would impact the country’s image, he said.  
